                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v04</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d623</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">623</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-09-19T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-09-19T16:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Hamilton, Maxwell M./9–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hulley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19T17:00:00-04:00">September 19, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. Please request <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> of Finnish Govt for the
                    Honorable Maxwell M. Hamilton as Envoy Extraordinary and Minister
                    Plenipotentiary near the Finnish Govt. Dept should be informed by telegraph as
                    soon as <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> has been given.<note n="9" xml:id="d623fn1">The Finnish Government’s <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi>
                        was received on October 4, 1945. Mr. Hamilton presented his credentials on
                        March 4, 1946.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
